        "generateUrl": "https://developers.enode.com/dashboard",
        "setup": "1. Sign up at [Enode Developers](https://developers.enode.com/register) and create an organization.\n2. In the [dashboard](https://developers.enode.com/dashboard), create a client with the right environment (`sandbox` for testing, `production` for live).\n3. Open the client’s [API credentials](https://developers.enode.com/dashboard) section to get the `client_id` and generate the `client_secret` with `Generate client secret`.\n4. Use these credentials with the OAuth 2.0 client credentials flow against the environment’s token URL to mint short-lived access tokens.\n5. Keep the `client_secret` server-side; regenerate it from the same credentials page if needed.",
